the 2., Danmarks dronning|edition=3rd|language=Danish|location=[[Copenhagen]] |publisher=[[Aschehoug]]|isbn=8711222832}}\n*{{cite book|last=Lyding|first=Henrik|date=2009 |title=Dronningens teater|language=Danish|location=[[Copenhagen]]|publisher=[[Gyldendal]] |isbn=9788702078787}}\n*{{cite book|last=Margrethe II |editor1-last=Andersen|editor1-first=Jens|year=2012|title=Om man s\u00e5 m\u00e5 sige, 350 Dronning Margrethe-citater |language=Danish|location=[[Copenhagen]]|publisher=[[Lindhardt og Ringhof]]|isbn=9788711394168}}\n*{{cite book|last=Rubinstein|first=Mogens|date=1996|title=Dronning Margrethe II, 25 \u00e5r som regent|language=Danish|location=[[Copenhagen]] |publisher=M\u00f8nterg\u00e5rden|isbn=8775535521}}\n*{{cite book|last=Skipper|first=Jon Bloch|date=2008|title=Tre s\u00f8stre, samtaler mellem dronning Margrethe, prinsesse Benedikte og dronning Anne-Marie |language=Danish|location=[[Copenhagen]]|publisher=[[Lindhardt og Ringhof]]|isbn=9788711300602}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Margrethe II of Denmark}}\n{{Wikiquote|Margrethe II of Denmark|Margrethe II}}\n* [http://kongehuset.dk/english/The-Royal-House/Regentparret/hm-the-queen The Queen's Homepage]\n* [http://kongehuset.dk/english The Official Website of The Danish Monarchy]\n* [http://arslonga.dk/DRONNINGENS_GOBELINER_Vikingetid.htm Tapestries for HM The Queen of Denmark]\n\n<!--Succession boxes-->\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-hou|[[House of Gl\u00fccksburg]]|16 April|1940|||[[House of Oldenburg]]}}\n{{s-break}}\n{{s-reg|}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Frederik IX]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Queen of Denmark]]|years=14 January 1972 \u2013 present}}\n{{s-inc|heir=[[Frederik, Crown Prince of Denmark|Frederik]]|heir-type=Heir apparent}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Monarchs of Denmark}}\n{{Danish princesses}}\n{{Current sovereigns}}\n{{Heads of state of the European Union Member states}}\n{{Members of the Spanish Order of the Golden Fleece}}\n{{Members of the Order of the Garter}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT: